<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="235" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,640,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Description</emphasis>
:—Herbs, perennial, 
<quantity box="[511,637,640,667]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="cm" value="85.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="20.0">20–150 cm</quantity>
tall. Rhizome woody, to 0.5 cm in diameter at base. Stems more or less branched, erect or ascending, pubescent or glabrous, reddish-brown or green. Basal stem leaves usually withered before anthesis, subsessile; middle stem leaves more or less sessile, leaf blade ovate, ovate-oblong or oblong, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="cm" value="12.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="4.0">4–20 cm</quantity>
long, 2.5– 
<quantity box="[290,343,748,775]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
broad, adaxially glabrous or sparsely pubescent, abaxially tomentose, 2- or 3-pinnatisect, segments 2–6 on each side, ovate-elliptic or oblong, lobules linear or linear-lanceolate, 8–25 (–35) mm long, 2.5–3.5 mm broad, rachis narrowly winged, apex acuminate, margin serrate, incised or entire, rarely revolute; uppermost leaves 1- or 2-pinnatisect, lobules linear or linear-lanceolate, margin serrate, incised or entire. Synflorescence a dense or sparse panicle. Capitula campanulate, subsessile, usually clustered together, 
<quantity box="[929,1024,892,919]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1099,1194,892,919]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
broad. Leaflike bracts linear or linear-lanceolate; phyllaries oblong-ovate or ovate, whitish, midribs green when fresh, margin membranous. Marginal female florets 6–12, white, fertile, 
<quantity box="[645,740,964,991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
long, corolla tubular, apex 2- or 3-toothed, style exerted; disk florets 10–20, white, bisexual, fertile, 
<quantity box="[563,656,1000,1027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
long, corolla tubular, apex 5-toothed. Achenes oblong.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="235" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,476,1036,1062]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[511,706,1036,1062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[511,706,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in western and southwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[1173,1263,1036,1062]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
and northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[136,225,1073,1099]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[236,303,1072,1098]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[318,401,1072,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1095,1117]" captionTargetBox="[203,1386,217,1042]" captionTargetId="figure-26@12.[170,1417,190,1071]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution of Artemisia fulgens var.fulgens (●) and A. fulgens var.meiguensis (■).Black arrow indicates the type locality of A. fulgens var. fulgens, i.e. Kangding county in Sichuan; blue arrow indicates the type locality of A. flaccida var. flaccida, i.e. Daxiangling in Hanyuan county in Sichuan; green arrow indicates the type locality of A. flaccida var. meiguensis (= A. fulgens var. meiguensis), i.e. Meigu county in Sichuan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362886/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). It grows by roadsides, at forest margins or on mountain slopes at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[1285,1443,1072,1099]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="m" value="2300.0" valueMax="3600.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–3600 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" box="[189,1025,1108,1135]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1108,1134]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering from August to November; fruiting in November.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,393,1144,1170]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Lectotypification</emphasis>
:—In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Pampanini (1930 a)" authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[673,1107,1144,1171]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[673,873,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia fulgens</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[890,1107,1144,1170]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="395 - 547" refId="ref7283" refString="Pampanini, R. (1930 a) Quinto contributo alla conoscenza dell' &quot; Artemisia verlotorum &quot; Lamotte. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (Nuova serie) 36: 395 - 547. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263503009439746" type="journal article" year="1930">Pampanini (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cited a single collection 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A.E. Pratt 88</emphasis>
(B, BM, E, K). As discussed by McNeil (2014), these sheets are 
<typeStatus box="[1001,1099,1181,1207]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">syntypes</typeStatus>
as 
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[1143,1360,1180,1206]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="395 - 547" refId="ref7283" refString="Pampanini, R. (1930 a) Quinto contributo alla conoscenza dell' &quot; Artemisia verlotorum &quot; Lamotte. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (Nuova serie) 36: 395 - 547. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263503009439746" type="journal article" year="1930">Pampanini (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate a type for 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[359,470,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[359,470,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We have been able to trace two sheets from E and K. Both are well preserved and match with the original description. According to ICN Art. 9.3 (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[780,1002,1252,1279]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" refId="ref7401" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[877,927,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), we have chosen the E sheet, on which the specimens are complete, as the 
<typeStatus box="[522,625,1288,1314]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[660,770,1288,1314]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[660,770,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[784,872,1288,1314]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1607,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,566,1579]" captionTargetId="figure-208@1.[170,1417,566,1579]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype (A) and isolectotype (B) sheets of Artemisia fulgens. Inset a: portion of a leaf, abaxially tomentose; inset b: capitula, showing the abaxially glabrous phyllaries." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362864/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), and cited the remaining duplicates as isolectotypes (the K sheet shown in 
<figureCitation box="[387,502,1324,1350]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1607,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,566,1579]" captionTargetId="figure-208@1.[170,1417,566,1579]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype (A) and isolectotype (B) sheets of Artemisia fulgens. Inset a: portion of a leaf, abaxially tomentose; inset b: capitula, showing the abaxially glabrous phyllaries." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362864/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
). We did not see the B and BM sheets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Handel-Mazzetti (1938)" authorityName=", Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1938" box="[417,904,1360,1387]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[417,622,1360,1386]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia flaccida</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Handel-Mazzetti, H." box="[635,904,1360,1386]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="203 - 360" refId="ref6716" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. (1938) Plantae sinenses a Dre. H. Smith annis 1921 - 22 et 1924 lectae. XXXII. Compositae 2. (ausgenommen Vernonia, Adenostemma, Tussilago, Cirsium, Gerbera, Myripnois, Taraxacum und Hieracium). Acta Horti Gothoburgensis 12: 203 - 360." type="journal article" year="1938">Handel-Mazzetti (1938)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cited a single collection, 
<emphasis box="[1187,1360,1360,1386]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">H. Smith 13540</emphasis>
. Eleven duplicates are deposited at A, BM, F, GB, MO, PE, S, UPS and W, respectively (four sheets shown in 
<figureCitation box="[1277,1373,1396,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[145,1442,190,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[145,1442,190,1958]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype (A) and isolectotype (B–D) sheets of Artemisia flaccida (= A. fulgens). A. Inset a: portion of a leaf, abaxially tomentose; inset b: capitula, showing the abaxially glabrous phyllaries." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362868/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). They are all well preserved and match with the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Handel-Mazzetti, H." box="[856,1127,1432,1458]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="203 - 360" refId="ref6716" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. (1938) Plantae sinenses a Dre. H. Smith annis 1921 - 22 et 1924 lectae. XXXII. Compositae 2. (ausgenommen Vernonia, Adenostemma, Tussilago, Cirsium, Gerbera, Myripnois, Taraxacum und Hieracium). Acta Horti Gothoburgensis 12: 203 - 360." type="journal article" year="1938">Handel-Mazzetti (1938)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate a type for 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1938" box="[136,260,1468,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[136,260,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. flaccida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the protologue, although in 1937 he annotated the UPS and S sheets as “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Hand." authorityName=", Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1938" box="[1155,1444,1468,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[1155,1364,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia flaccida</emphasis>
Hand.
</taxonomicName>
- Mzt., spec. nov., Typus” on the determination slips (
<figureCitation box="[722,844,1504,1531]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[145,1442,190,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[145,1442,190,1958]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype (A) and isolectotype (B–D) sheets of Artemisia flaccida (= A. fulgens). A. Inset a: portion of a leaf, abaxially tomentose; inset b: capitula, showing the abaxially glabrous phyllaries." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362868/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Fig. 3A, B</figureCitation>
). As discussed by McNeil (2014), all the sheets of the collection 
<emphasis box="[253,428,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">H. Smith 13540</emphasis>
are 
<typeStatus box="[477,579,1541,1567]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">syntypes</typeStatus>
. We have designated the UPS sheet, with a photograph of it in the protologue, as the 
<typeStatus box="[208,311,1576,1602]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1938" box="[348,469,1576,1602]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[348,469,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. flaccida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and cited the duplicates at A, BM, F, GB, MO, PE, S and W as isolectotypes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,640,2071]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,1612,1638]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Notes</emphasis>
:—In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[505,721,1612,1638]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="395 - 547" refId="ref7283" refString="Pampanini, R. (1930 a) Quinto contributo alla conoscenza dell' &quot; Artemisia verlotorum &quot; Lamotte. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (Nuova serie) 36: 395 - 547. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263503009439746" type="journal article" year="1930">Pampanini (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
referred 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[828,1027,1612,1638]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[828,1027,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<emphasis box="[1067,1084,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Besser (1829: 222)" authorityName="Besser" authorityPageNumber="222" authorityYear="1829" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Abrotanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1285,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Abrotanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Besser, W. S." pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="219 - 265" refId="ref6614" refString="Besser, W. S. (1829) Lettre de Mr. le Dr. Besser au directeur monsieur le directeur. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 1: 219 - 265." type="journal article" year="1829">Besser (1829: 222)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Handel-Mazzetti, H." box="[202,472,1648,1674]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="203 - 360" refId="ref6716" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. (1938) Plantae sinenses a Dre. H. Smith annis 1921 - 22 et 1924 lectae. XXXII. Compositae 2. (ausgenommen Vernonia, Adenostemma, Tussilago, Cirsium, Gerbera, Myripnois, Taraxacum und Hieracium). Acta Horti Gothoburgensis 12: 203 - 360." type="journal article" year="1938">Handel-Mazzetti (1938)</bibRefCitation>
also referred it, under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1938" box="[838,960,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaccida">
<emphasis box="[838,960,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. flaccida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to this section. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ling, Y. R." box="[1145,1279,1648,1674]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 253" refId="ref6999" refString="Ling, Y. R. (1991) Artemisia L. In: Ling, Y. &amp; Ling, Y. R. (Eds.) Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol. 76 (2). Science Press, Beijing, pp. 1 - 253." type="book chapter" year="1991">Ling (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ling, Y. R. &amp; Humphries, C. J. &amp; Gilbert, M. G." pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="676 - 737" refId="ref7139" refString="Ling, Y. R., Humphries, C. J. &amp; Gilbert, M. G. (2011) Artemisia Linnaeus. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Eds.) Flora of China, vol. 20 - 21. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, pp. 676 - 737." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Ling 
<emphasis box="[1395,1452,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
placed this species within 
<emphasis box="[509,526,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[598,707,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[598,707,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Indeed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[810,922,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[810,922,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to species in this section in having 1- or 2-pinnatisect leaves and linear or linear-lanceolate lobules, but actually this species should be closer to those in 
<emphasis box="[1427,1444,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis box="[193,325,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Albibractea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ling, Y. R." box="[331,520,1756,1783]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="504 - 513" refId="ref6817" refString="Ling, Y. R. (1980) Taxa nova generum Artemisiae et Seriphidii xizangensis. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 18: 504 - 513." type="journal article" year="1980">Ling (1980: 506)</bibRefCitation>
by having whitish phyllaries and white florets, and thus may better be placed within this section. In 
<emphasis box="[307,324,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis box="[395,527,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">Albibractea</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pampanini" authorityYear="1930" box="[541,653,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[541,653,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wallich ex Candolle (1938: 115)" authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityPageNumber="115" authorityYear="1938" box="[945,1451,1792,1819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lactiflora">
<emphasis box="[945,962,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[976,1080,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">lactiflora</emphasis>
Wallich ex Candolle (1938: 115)
</taxonomicName>
in having 1- or 2-pinnatisect leaves and campanulate capitula, but differs by having abaxially tomentose (vs. sparsely pubescent or glabrous) leaves, and entire, serrate or incised (vs. irregularly serrate) lobules. In the shape of leaf lobules, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. Q. Guo, L. Wang &amp; Q. E. Yang" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="X. Q. Guo, L. Wang &amp; Q. E. Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[136,426,1900,1927]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fulgens" variety="meiguensis">
<emphasis box="[136,248,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. fulgens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[302,426,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">meiguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Ling" authorityYear="1988" box="[464,764,1900,1927]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="flaccida" variety="meiguensis">
<emphasis box="[464,585,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. flaccida</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[640,764,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">meiguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is rather similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pampanini 1927: 675) Ling &amp; Ling" authorityName="Ling &amp; Ling" baseAuthorityName="Pampanini" baseAuthorityPageNumber="675" baseAuthorityYear="1927" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lactiflora" variety="incisa">
<emphasis box="[989,1006,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1020,1124,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">lactiflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1179,1246,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">incisa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="632 - 708" refId="ref7254" refString="Pampanini, R. (1927) Materiali per lo studio delle Artemisie asiatiche. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (Nouva serie) 34: 632 - 708." type="journal article" year="1927">Pampanini 1927: 675</bibRefCitation>
) Ling &amp; Ling
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ling, Y. R." box="[370,563,1936,1962]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref6919" refString="Ling, Y. R. (1988 a) The Chinese Artemisia Linn. -- the classification, distribution and application of Artemisia Linn. in China. Bulletin of Botanical Research (Harbin) 8 (4): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1988">Ling (1988a: 42)</bibRefCitation>
. The leaf lobules of the former are serrate or incised, whereas those of the latter are irregularly serrate. Geographically 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityYear="1938" box="[584,722,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lactiflora">
<emphasis box="[584,722,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">A. lactiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in southern 
